@node description "Description"

    ArexxGuide online help for CygnusEd v3.5.

    Press a key and the script will search ArexxGuide for the node
    corresponding to the word under the cursor, convert it to ascii and
    load it into CED.

    Optional saving of ascii nodes for much faster loading next time you
    need the information.

    In addition to ArexxGuide arx_help.ced will also search any other
    crossreference (@{" xref " link xref}) files that you have installed. So you 
    can also get online help for other Arexx function libraries or use it as
    an AutoDoc lookup tool.

@endnode
@node requirements "Requirements"

    CygnusEd 3.5
    ArexxGuide 2.0a (Aminet: util/rexx/arexxguide*).

@endnode
@node installation "Installation"

    Copy arx_help.ced to rexx:

    ArexxGuide must be set up correctly (Use the ARx_Setup.rexx script).
    The environment variable env:AmigaGuide/path must include the directory
    where arx_guide.xref is located. And env:ARexxGuide/AGCmd must hold the
    name of your amigaguide viewer. But the ArexxGuide setup script takes
    care of all that.

    Copy ARx_Guide.xref from the xref drawer to where you've placed the
    original when installing ArexxGuide. This file contains a workaround for
    the WB 3.0/3.1 AmigaGuide @{" bug " link agbug}.

    Have a look in the xref drawer. If you want online help for something
    not included in ArexxGuide then copy the relevant @{" .xref file(s)" link xref}
    somewhere and make sure that the environment variable
    env:ArexxGuide/xrfiles includes the complete path to these files.

    Install the script on one of the FKeys in CED or bind it to any other
    key with a long invocation macro like this:
    - Start long-term invocation macro.
    - Select 'HELP' (Or something else) as hotkey.
    - Select Send Dos/Arexx command.
    - Enter 'arx_help.ced' in the. Don't put 'rx' in front or anything else. 
    - Finish the macro and save it.

    There is one commandline option - FORCEAGCMD - see @{" usage " link usage} for more 
    information.

@endnode
@node configuration "Configuration"

    If you want to enable saving of ascii nodes (See @{" usage " link usage}) you have to
    edit the 'ascdir' line at the start of the script and make sure that the
    directory you specify exists. 

@endnode
@node usage "Usage"

    The FORCEAGCMD switch forces the use of your regular AmigaGuide viewer.
    Usefull if you want to browse the guide for a while or want access to 
    nodes not found in the xref file.
    I have 'arx_help.ced' installed on the HELP key and 'arx_help.ced
    FORCEAGCMD' on shift-HELP.

    If ArexxGuide is already running _or_ you want to view the ArexxGuide
    index the node will be shown with your regular AmigaGuide viewer (As
    defined in env:ARexxGuide/AGCmd).

    If you start the script while the cursor is on an empty line, you will
    be presented with a string requester. Just type any in any Arexx 
    keyword, press OK, and the according help text will pop up.

    The searching and guide > ascii conversion is not that fast. So if you
    have room enough on your harddisk I recommend turning the saving of
    ascii nodes on (See @{" configuration " link configuration}).
    The script will now save the ascii node to the directory you specify and 
    next time you need the information it will load it directly from there. 
    And that's pretty fast :-) 

    Converted AmigaGuide links in the ascii node is shown enclosed in '{}'
    brackets. You can use these for further browsing from CED

@endnode
@node xref "xref"

    I've included some additional crossreference files in the xref drawer:
    
    @{" ARx_Guide.xref      " link xref/arx_guide.xref/main} Read about the WB 3.0/3.1 AmigaGuide @{" bug " link agbug}.
    @{" autodocs.xref       " link xref/autodocs.xref/main} AutoDocs crossreference.
    @{" RexxLocalDates.xref " link xref/RexxLocalDates.xref/main} Anders Wegge Jakobsen's rexxlocaldates.library.
    @{" RexxReqTools.xref   " link xref/RexxReqTools.xref/main} Rafael D'Halleweyn's rexxreqtools.library.
    @{" rexxtricks.xref     " link xref/rexxtricks.xref/main} Jürgen Kohrmeyer's rexxtricks.library.

    Read @{" installation " link installation} for how to install the xref files and get online
    help for the corresponding libraries.

    NOTE: If you install all the additional xref files (Especially the 35kb
    autodocs.xref) you'll notice that arx_help is rather slow the first time
    you run it. This is because it takes some time to load the xref files.
    But once loaded they stay in memory, so next time you use it it's back
    to normal speed.

@endnode
@node agbug "WB 3.0/3.1 AmigaGuide bug"

    The amigaguide.library in WB 3.0 and 3.1 has a slight bug. It 
    can't find the last entry in an xref file when using the GetXRef Arexx
    function

    Here's an example. If you wanted help for PARSEDATE, GetXRef would
    return '10' (Not Found) and arx_ced would therefore report 'PARSEDATE
    not found':

    XREF:
    OPENLOCALE       "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    CLOSELOCALE      "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    GETLOCALESTRING  "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    GETLOCALEVARS    "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    FORMATDATE       "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    PARSEDATE        "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    #

    I've solved the problem by adding a dummy last entry:

    PARSEDATE        "RexxLocalDates.guide" 0 1
    ¤¤¤DUMMY¤¤¤      "dummy.guide" 0 0
    #

    to all the @{" xref files " link xref} in the xref drawer. Including the
    xref file for ArexxGuide itself - so make sure that you install at least
    that. One day you might need online help for XRANGE() :-) 

@endnode
